-- HA-00101 ("Using the LEAP Assistant"): document multi-record batch creation
-- (one confirmation, dependency-ordered, no-holes field gathering) and the
-- Open-record links the assistant shows after a successful create.
update help_articles
set ha_body_markdown = ha_body_markdown || E'\n\n## Creating several related records at once\n\nYou can ask the assistant to set up a whole group of related records in one request — for example, an account together with its property, a building, and a contact. The assistant plans the entire set and creates the records together, in the right order, so the property is linked to the account, the building to the property, and the contact to the account automatically. You confirm the whole plan once with **Confirm all** rather than approving each record separately.\n\nBefore it builds anything, the assistant checks what each record requires and fills in everything it can. If something required is missing — most commonly a property ZIP code, or how to split a person''s name — it asks you for just those details in a single question, so nothing is created with empty required fields. A few things it handles automatically: it converts a spelled-out state (e.g. "Wisconsin") to its two-letter code, names an unlabeled building "Building 1", and splits a full name into first and last name.\n\nIf one record in the batch can''t be created, the assistant stops at that point and tells you which step failed, so you never end up with a half-finished set of records.\n\n## Opening a record the assistant created\n\nWhen the assistant creates a record, it shows an **Open <record>** link for it right in the conversation — one link per record when it created several. Select the link to jump straight to the new record. You can also copy the record''s address from your browser once it''s open to share it with a coworker.'
    ha_updated_at = now()
where ha_slug='using-the-leap-assistant';
